Asperthecin production in ISS-grown LO1362 and CW12001. 
a
 LC-MS profiles depicting asperthecin production after 7 days of growth on the ISS, as detected by UV total scan. 
b
 Quantification of asperthecin production showing percent change for ISS-grown samples relative to Earth-grown counterparts. Significance was determined using Welch’s t-test. 
